    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1055"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1055">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 332.115W31.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">O’Shaughnessy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following cable sent to Tampico and to Department’s representative at El Paso
                    with instructions to unofficially present same to Carranza and to say Department
                    hopes he will give those under his control instructions to observe strictly the
                    recommendations herein set forth:</p>
                <p>[Here follows telegram sent to Tampico April 9, 1914.]</p>
                <p>Present above to proper authorities and endeavor to secure issuance of necessary
                    orders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
